        <abstract> 
<p>THF’s article in <hi rend="italic">Nature</hi> ["The fertilisation of a few papilionaceous flowers", 6 (1872): 478–80, 498–501] is extremely good.</p> 
            <p>Suspects he now has answer to why common peas and sweetpeas hardly ever intercross, a point which half drove CD mad for years.</p>
        </abstract>
